				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm afraid about that in a certain way.
<br />
I remember a great scene from the movie: "Back to the Future".
<br />

<br />
You know this scene where Michael J. Fox is in front of an arcade video game and play with pistols. Then two children arrive and want to play too. But when they see the machine, one of them says: "Oh suck, you need to play with your hands ?! No way". Or something like that. 
<br />

<br />
I've been really disturbed by this sequence, cause atm i cant imagine a game without a mouse or a keyboard. I like the feeling, the control. And i fear to not be able to enjoy a game that could be controlled by the mind only, or a tracking system based on your eye movements.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
